%20of%20the%20lander.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65018658992da60019eb41f8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20annotated%20image%20shows%20an%20astronaut%20waving%20next%20to%20the%20Apollo%2016%20lander.%20Scientist%20have%20found%20a%20similar%20lander%2C%20from%20the%20Apollo%2017%20missions%2C%20caused%20unexplained%20mini-quakes%20on%20the%20surface%20of%20the%20moon.%3Cp%3ENASA%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EData%20showed%20a%20mysterious%20quake%20happening%20every%20lunar%20morning%2C%20and%20scientists%20weren't%20sure%20why.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20new%20study%20has%20found%20morning%20tremors%20are%20coming%20from%20the%20Apollo%2017%20lunar%20lander%20base.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20lander%20base%20expands%20and%20vibrates%20every%20morning%20as%20it%20gets%20heated%20by%20the%20sun.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20baffled%20by%20mysterious%20daily%20quakes%20on%20the%20surface%20of%20the%20moon%20have%20traced%20back%20their%20origin%20to%20an%20unexpected%20source.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20from%20NASA%20and%20the%20California%20Institute%20of%20Technology%20reanalyzed%20data%20on%20tiny%20moonquakes%2C%20which%20was%20gathered%20in%20the%201970s%20by%20astronauts%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapollo-17-astronauts-moon-landing-last-manned-lunar-mission-pictures-2019-12%5C%22%3EApollo%2017%C2%A0%20mission.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20discovered%20that%20some%20of%20the%20tremors%20were%20being%20produced%20by%20the%20descent%20stage%20of%20the%20Apollo%2017%20lunar%20module%2C%20left%20behind%20on%20the%20lunar%20surface%2051%20years%20ago.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEvery%20lunar%20morning%20when%20the%20sun%20hits%20the%20lander%2C%20it%20starts%20popping%20off%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Allen%20Husker%2C%20research%20professor%20of%20geophysics%20and%20coauthor%20of%20the%20new%20study%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.caltech.edu%2Fabout%2Fnews%2Fthe-lunar-alarm-clock-new-study-characterizes-regular-moonquakes%5C%22%3Ein%20a%20press%20release.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20moon%20doesn't%20have%20tectonic%20activity%2C%20but%20it's%20still%20shaking%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20goal%20of%20the%20Apollo%20mission%20%E2%80%94%20which%20put%20the%20first%20humans%20on%20the%20moon%20and%20ran%20from%201961%20to%201972%20%E2%80%94%20was%20to%20collect%20information%20about%20the%20moon's%20seismic%20activity.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20do%20so%2C%20astronauts%20placed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmars-quakes-nasa-insight-not-like-earthquakes-2019-7%5C%22%3Eseismic%20detectors%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20moon%20over%20the%20course%20of%20Apollo%20missions%2011%20to%2017.%20The%20Apollo%20mission%20seismometers%20stopped%20being%20operational%20in%201977%2C%20but%20scientists%20have%20continued%20to%20re-analyze%20the%20data%20to%20gain%20crucial%20clues%20about%20how%20our%20satellite%20cracks%20and%20stretches.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222628%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22astronaut%20in%20spacesuit%20sits%20on%20lunar%20rover%20vehicle%20platform%20with%20wheels%20on%20the%20moon%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F650195ac992da60019eb4b59%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221971%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20astronaut%20is%20seen%20riding%20a%20lunar%20rover%20during%20the%20Apollo%2017%20mission.%3Cp%3ENASA%2FHarrison%20H.%20Schmitt%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20thanks%20to%20these%20readings%20that%20scientists%20first%20gained%20an%20understanding%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Findias-moon-lander-detects-signs-of-possible-moonquake-2023-9%5C%22%3Emoonquakes.%3C%2Fa%3E%20Unlike%20on%20Earth%2C%20tremors%20on%20the%20moon%20have%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20tectonic%20plate%20shifting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20a%20quake%20happens%20on%20the%20moon%2C%20it's%20due%20to%20one%20of%20three%20factors%3A%20a%20meteor%20hits%20the%20surface%2C%20the%20Earth's%20gravity%20stretches%20or%20squeezes%20the%20moon's%20interior%2C%20or%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-moon-is-shrinking-like-raisin-producing-moonquakes-2019-5%5C%22%3Emoon's%20surface%20bakes%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0under%20the%20intense%20sunlight%20hitting%20it%20during%20the%20day%2C%20a%20post%20from%20the%20European%20commission%20explained.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%20scientists%20were%20so%20surprised%20when%20they%20saw%20the%20unusual%20readings%20when%20reanalyzing%20the%20data%20from%20the%20Apollo%2017%20seismic%20detectors%3A%20they%20saw%20quakes%20that%20had%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20these%20three%20causes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20lunar%20lander%20is%20creaking%20in%20the%20hot%20sun%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20quakes%20had%20never%20been%20spotted%20before%2C%20even%20though%20the%20data%20was%20captured%20between%20October%201976%20to%20May%201977.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20because%20the%20readings%20from%20the%20Apollo%2017%20mission%20were%20very%20messy%20and%20difficult%20to%20interpret%2C%20the%20Caltech%20and%20NASA%20scientists%20said%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fagupubs.onlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1029%2F2022JE007704%5C%22%3Ea%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20presenting%20their%20findings%2C%20which%20was%20published%20in%20the%20peer-reviewed%20journal%20JGR%20Planets%20on%20Sept%205.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsing%20machine%20learning%20they%20were%20able%20to%20clean%20up%20the%20data.%20As%20they%20expected%2C%20they%20picked%20up%20readings%20from%20so-called%20thermal%20quakes%20that%20happen%20in%20the%20afternoon%20when%20the%20moon%20starts%20to%20cool.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20each%20morning%2C%20scientists%20also%20saw%20bizarre%20waves%20popping%20up%20every%20few%20minutes.%20By%20triangulating%20the%20signal%2C%20they%20were%20able%20to%20figure%20out%20the%20source%20of%20the%20mysterious%20tremors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20found%20that%20impulsive%20moonquakes%20are%20not%20due%20to%20natural%20processes%2C%20but%20are%20vibrations%20generated%20from%20the%20lunar%20module%20descent%20vehicle%20left%20by%20the%20astronauts%20in%201972%2C%26quot%3B%20Husker%20said%20in%20the%20study%20with%20co-authors%20Francesco%20Civilini%2C%20from%20Caltech%20and%20Renee%20Weber%20of%20the%20NASA%20Marshall%20Space%20Flight%20Center.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Apollo%2017%20astronauts%20lifted%20off%20from%20the%20moon%20in%201972%2C%20they%20left%20behind%20part%20of%20the%20lunar%20lander%20%E2%80%94%20you%20can%20see%20this%20in%20the%20video%20below.%20It%20turns%20out%20that%20hunk%20of%20metal%20is%20what%20was%20causing%20these%20mysterious%20quakes%2C%20as%20it%20boils%20and%20creaks%20as%20temperatures%20range%20from%20%2B250%20to%20-208%C2%B0%20F%2C%20per%20the%20press%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22youtube%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%20%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F9HQfauGJaTs%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Ch2%3EThis%20is%20important%20information%20for%20upcoming%20missions%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGoing%20to%20the%20moon%20always%20comes%20with%20a%20certain%20number%20of%20unknowns%2C%20for%20a%20very%20simple%20reason%3A%20we%20haven't%20been%20to%20the%20moon%20very%20many%20times.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20don't%20have%20a%20very%20good%20idea%20of%20what%20happens%20to%20space%20gear%20if%20it's%20left%20on%20the%20moon%20for%20a%20very%20long%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20information%20is%20quite%20important%20because%20NASA%20is%20aiming%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoon-missions-why-astronauts-have-not-returned-2018-7%5C%22%3Ego%20back%20to%20the%20moon%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%2050%20years%2C%20and%20this%20time%2C%20it%20wants%20astronauts%20to%20stay%20there%20for%20an%20extended%20period%20of%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20data%20provides%20rare%20information%20on%20what%20happens%20to%20a%20spaceship%20that's%20left%20to%20bake%20in%20the%20sun%2C%20which%20can%20be%20incorporated%20when%20designing%20new%20tech%2C%20per%20the%20CalTech%20press%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20important%20because%20a%20lot%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fno-gps-on-moon-nasa-esa-artemis-plans-to-fix-2023-1%5C%22%3Efuture%20planned%20missions%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20going%20toward%20the%20south%20pole%20of%20the%20moon%2C%20which%20never%20sees%20sunlight%2C%20Husker%20said%20in%20the%20press%20release.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmysterious-moonquakes-old-apollo-landing-site-nasa-lunar-tremors-source-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694608242000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65018676992da60019eb4212%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmysterious-moonquakes-old-apollo-landing-site-nasa-lunar-tremors-source-2023-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Scientists%20have%20discovered%20that%20tiny%20moonquakes%20are%20being%20produced%20from%20the%20left-behind%20descent%20stage%20of%20the%20Apollo%2017%20lunar%20module.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mguenot%40businessinsider.com%20(Marianne%20Guenot)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmysterious-moonquakes-old-apollo-landing-site-nasa-lunar-tremors-source-2023-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22iSpot%20Buys%20605%20in%20Bid%20for%20TV-Measurement%20Market%20Edge%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A16946079