n%20talks%20to%20refinance%20%243.5%20bn%20debt%20taken%20for%20Ambuja%20takeover%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694606298000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-08%2F14%2Ffull%2F1691975779-7461.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fadani-group-in-talks-to-refinance-3-5-bn-debt-taken-for-ambuja-takeover-123091300875_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Indian%20conglomerate%20backed%20by%20billionaire%20Gautam%20Adani%20has%20been%20in%20talks%20with%20lenders%20for%20several%20months%20as%20it%20seeks%20to%20refinance%20as%20much%20as%20%243.8%20billion%20worth%20of%20debt%20taken%20for%20Ambuja%20acquisition%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fadani-group-in-talks-to-refinance-3-5-bn-debt-taken-for-ambuja-takeover-123091300875_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fadani-group-in-talks-to-refinance-3-5-bn-debt-taken-for-ambuja-takeover-123091300875_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fadani-group-in-talks-to-refinance-3-5-bn-debt-taken-for-ambuja-takeover-123091300875_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Centre's%20Report%20Says%20India%20Has%20150%20Elephant%20Corridors%2C%20Most%20Are%20In...%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20at%20least%20150%20elephant%20corridors%20spanning%2015%20range-states%20across%20four%20elephant-bearing%20regions.%20West%20Bengal%20topps%20the%20list%20with%2026%20such%20land%20strips%2C%20according%20to%20a%20new%20Union%20Environment%20Ministry%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20central%20government's%202010%20Elephant%20Task%20Force%20report%20(Gajah%20report)%20listed%2088%20corridors%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20report%2C%20titled%20%26quot%3BElephant%20Corridors%20of%20India%26quot%3B%2C%20also%20highlights%20that%20the%20intensity%20of%20elephant%20use%20has%20increased%20in%2059%20of%20these%20corridors%2C%20remained%20stable%20in%2029%20and%20decreased%20in%2029%20others.%20Of%20the%20total%20corridors%2C%2015%20have%20been%20impaired%20and%20require%20restoration%20efforts%20to%20restore%20functionality.%20Information%20regarding%20the%20current%20use%20of%2018%20corridors%20by%20elephants%20was%20unavailable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20elephant%20corridor%20is%20a%20land%20strip%20facilitating%20the%20movement%20of%20elephants%20between%20two%20or%20more%20viable%20habitat%20patches.%20Corridors%20leading%20the%20animals%20away%20from%20forest%20habitats%20into%20the%20human%20domain%20without%20connecting%20to%20viable%20habitat%20patches%20are%20not%20considered%20true%20elephant%20corridors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDemographic%20isolation%20and%20genetic%20viability%20concerns%20pose%20an%20extinction%20risk%20to%20elephant%20populations.%20Therefore%2C%20safeguarding%20elephant%20corridors%20is%20a%20key%20conservation%20strategy%2C%20the%20report%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20last%20estimation%20conducted%20in%202017%2C%20there%20are%20around%2030%2C000%20elephants%20in%20India%2C%20which%20account%20for%2060%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20animal's%20global%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20report%20is%20an%20outcome%20of%20a%20collaborative%20effort%20between%20the%20Union%20Environment%20Ministry's%20Project%20Elephant%20and%20state%20forest%20departments%2C%20with%20technical%20support%20from%20the%20Wildlife%20Institute%20of%20India.%20Ground%20validation%20of%20the%20150%20elephant%20corridors%20across%2015%20states%20took%20nearly%20two%20years%20to%20complete.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWest%20Bengal%20leads%20with%20the%20highest%20number%20of%20elephant%20corridors%20in%20India%2C%20accounting%20for%20over%2017%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20total%20such%20land%20patches%20in%20the%20country%2C%20the%20report%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20four%20elephant-bearing%20regions%20in%20India%2C%20the%20east-central%20region%20reported%20the%20highest%20number%20of%20elephant%20corridors%20at%2052%2C%20followed%20by%20the%20northeast%20region%20with%2048%20and%20the%20southern%20region%20with%2032.%20The%20northern%20region%20has%20the%20lowest%20number%20of%20elephant%20corridors%20at%2018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20150%20reported%20elephant%20corridors%2C%20126%20are%20within%20the%20political%20boundaries%20of%20states%20while%2019%20are%20located%20across%20two%20states.%20There%20are%20also%20six%20trans-national%20corridors%20between%20India%20and%20Nepal%2C%20primarily%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20says%20that%20there%20are%20states%20where%20elephants%20have%20recently%20expanded%20their%20ranges.%20These%20include%20the%20Vidarbha%20region%20in%20Maharashtra%20adjoining%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20southern%20Maharashtra%20adjoining%20Karnataka%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20-%20where%20elephants%20presently%20occur%20in%20Bandhavgarh%20and%20Sanjay%20tiger%20reserves%20-%20and%20northern%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20where%20elephants%20move%20in%20from%20Odisha.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20these%20states%2C%20assessing%20the%20long-term%20viability%20of%20habitats%20to%20support%20elephant%20populations%20and%20adopting%20a%20data-driven%20approach%20to%20identify%20corridors%20is%20crucial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20states%20data%20on%20elephant%20movement%20remains%20limited%20in%20many%20northeastern%20states%20that%20host%20relatively%20small%20elephant%20populations.%20Collaborative%20efforts%20between%20state%20forest%20departments%20and%20Project%20Elephant%20could%20clarify%20the%20corridor%20status%20in%20these%20areas%20in%20the%20coming%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20