%20did%20come%20in%20continues%20to%20show%20underlying%20resilience%20in%20the%20economy.%20It%20is%20not%20an%20overly%20strong%20economy%20but%20also%20not%20one%20where%20there%20are%20clear%20signs%20of%20a%20recession%2C%20or%20a%20significant%20slowdown%20of%20any%20kind%20is%20at%20hand%2C%26quot%3B%20Siegel%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESiegel%20has%20been%20among%20the%20more%20bullish%20economic%20commentators%20lately%2C%20recently%20highlighting%20the%20nation's%20%26quot%3Bamazing%20resilience%26quot%3B%20despite%20the%20Federal%20Reserve's%20aggressive%20interest-rate%20increases%20over%20the%20six%20quarters%20aimed%20at%20taming%20inflation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20previously%20stated%20that%20US%20equities%20are%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fsiegel-wharton-stock-market-outlook-house-prices-mortgages-fed-inflation-2023-9%5C%22%3Esolid%20footing%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20the%20inflation%20threat%20is%20fading%2C%20meaning%20the%20Fed%20may%20be%20able%20to%20soon%20start%20loosening%20monetary%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20highly%20unlikely%20for%20the%20Fed%20to%20increase%20rates%20in%20September%2C%20and%20while%20the%20markets%20have%20priced%20in%20some%20probability%20of%20a%20November%20hike%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20the%20Fed%20needs%20to%20make%20that%20move%2C%26quot%3B%20Siegel%20said%20in%20his%20most%20recent%20commentary.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20equities%2C%20I%20still%20see%20an%20upward%20tilt%20for%20the%20remainder%20of%20the%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20stocks%20have%20surged%20this%20year%20thanks%20to%20investor%20excitement%20about%20artificial%20intelligence%20%E2%80%93%20and%20hopes%20that%20it%20the%20groundbreaking%20technology%20will%20boost%20productivity%20and%20prop%20up%20corporate%20profits.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInsider's%20Matthew%20Fox%20reported%20that%20stocks%20could%20hit%20new%20highs%20by%20the%20en