te%20interview%20to%20Karan%20Thapar%20for%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EWire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20to%20mark%20the%20publication%20of%20his%20latest%20book%20%3Cem%3EYou%20Must%20Know%20Your%20Constitution%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Nariman%20said%20that%20it%20is%20impossible%20to%20write%20a%20new%20constitution%20in%20the%20atmosphere%20that%20prevails%20in%20the%20country%20today.%20He%20said%20the%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20spirit%20of%20tolerance%20and%20accommodation%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20is%20necessary%20for%20writing%20a%20constitution%2C%20is%20missing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20about%20comments%20made%20by%20former%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%2C%20Ranjan%20Gogoi%2C%20that%20the%20constitution%20does%20not%20have%20a%20basic%20structure%2C%20Nariman%20said%20whilst%20everyone%20is%20entitled%20to%20his%20view%20Justice%20Gogoi%E2%80%99s%20view%20is%20%E2%80%9Cwrong%E2%80%9D.%20Nariman%20gave%20fascinating%20details%20of%20how%2C%20under%20Chief%20Justice%20Ray%20in%201975%2C%20a%20bench%20was%20set%20up%20to%20reconsider%20the%20basic%20structure%20doctrine%20of%201973%20but%20after%20two%20days%20of%20hearings%20was%20dissolved%20without%20explanation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EQuoting%20Seervai%2C%20Nariman%20said%20the%20bench%20was%20dissolved%20because%20CJI%20Ray%20realised%20that%2012%20out%20of%2013%20judges%20hearing%20the%20matter%20were%20firmly%20in%20support%20of%20the%20basic%20structure%20doctrine%20and%20he%20would%20be%20reduced%20to%20a%20minority%20of%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENariman%20argued%20that%20it%20is%20judicial%20interpretation%20of%20the%20constitution%20that%20is%20it%E2%80%99s%20breadth%20of%20life.%20He%20says%20it%E2%80%99s%20interpretation%20by%20judges%20that%20make%20the%20phrase%20%E2%80%98We%20the%20people%E2%80%99%20relevant%20to%20generations%20born%20after%201950.%20He%20says%20it%E2%80%99s%20the%20duty%20of%20judges%20to%20interpret%20the%20constitution%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20time%20and%20the%20issues%20of%20the%20day.%20Literalistic%20%C2%A0interpretation%2C%20as%20is%20the%20present%20fashion%20in%20the%20United%20States%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20is%20not%20something%20he%20endorses%20or%20subscribes%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%E2%80%99s%20a%20sizeable%20section%20of%20the%20interview%20where%20Nariman%20discusses%20the%20fact%20that%20often%20judges%2C%20even%20at%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20level%2C%20fail%20to%20stand%20up%20for%20the%20rights%20the%20constitution%20has%20conferred%20on%20citizens.%20This%20discussion%20also%20includes%20a%20sizeable%20section%20about%20how%20the%20present%20Collegium%20allows%20itself%20to%20be%20overruled%20by%20the%20government%20in%20appointment%20of%20judges%20and%20transfer%20of%20judges.%20Justice%20Muralidhar%E2%80%99s%20case%20is%20discussed%2C%20in%20particular.%20Nariman%20believes%20that%20this%20is%20%E2%80%9Cparticularly%20sad%E2%80%9D.%20He%20agrees%20that%20when%20judges%20fail%20to%20stand%20up%20for%20their%20own%20rights%20(to%20appoint%20judges)%20it%20shows%20a%20lack%20of%20spine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20questions%20asked%20to%20Nariman%20were%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E1)%20Let%E2%80%99s%20start%20with%20issues%20and%20concerns%20you%20raise%20about%20the%20constitution%20before%20we%20come%20to%20issues%20and%20concerns%20about%20the%20way%20the%20constitution%20has%20been%20implemented%20and%20adhered%20to%20by%20our%20politicians.%20First%2C%20you%20say%20in%20Chapter%203%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20preamble%20is%20the%20most%20important%20part%20of%20the%20constitution%E2%80%9D.%20Given%20that%20most%20people%20ignore%20it%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20been%20amended%20by%20Indira%20Gandhi%20%E2%80%93%20and%20some%20would%20say%20controversially%20%E2%80%93%20why%20do%20you%20think%20it%E2%80%99s%20the%20most%20important%20part%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E2)%20Now%20you%20also%20believe%20%E2%80%93%20and%20for%20some%20this%20may%20be%20controversial%20%E2%80%93%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20the%20way%20judges%20%E2%80%9Chave%20interpreted%20and%20helped%20sustain%20a%20constitution%20that%20had%20been%20framed%20for%20only%20350%20million%20people%2C%20most%20of%20whom%20are%20not%20even%20alive%20today%20%E2%80%A6%20(that)%20is%20one%20of%20the%20ways%20in%20which%20a%20written%20constitution%20is%20made%20to%20grow%20into%20a%20dynamic%20living%20document%E2%80%9D.%20Can%20you%20explain%20this%20further%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E3)%20So%20I%20take%20it%20you%20do%20not%20accept%20literalistic%20interpretations%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20as%20we%20increasingly%20see%20in%20the%20United%20States%20Supreme%20Court%3F%20You%20believe%20that%20each%20generation%20must%20interpret%20the%20constitution%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20time%20and%20the%20issues%20of%20the%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E4)%20This%20brings%20me%20to%20an%20issue%20that%20has%20suddenly%20acquired%20considerable%20salience%20after%20a%20former%20Chief%20Justice%20questioned%20whether%20there%E2%80%99s%20such%20a%20thing%20as%20a%20basic%20structure%20of%20our%20constitution.%20Your%20book%20cites%20not%20only%20the%20Keshavananda%20Bharti%20case%20but%20several%20other%20instances%2C%20such%20as%20Bhim%20Singh%2C%20Kuldeep%20Nayyar%2C%20Indira%20Gandhi%20vs.%20Raj%20Narain%20and%2C%20of%20course%2C%20the%20National%20Judicial%20Commission%20case%2C%20where%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20clearly%20ruled%20that%20there%20is%20a%20basic%20structure.%20So%20how%20would%20you%20respond%20to%20the%20doubts%20Chief%20Justice%20Gogoi%20has%20raised%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E5)%20Would%20One%20Nation%20One%20Election%20breach%20the%20basic%20structure%20because%20it%20requires%20state%20assemblies%20to%20synchronize%20with%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%3F%20And%2C%20secondly%2C%20because%20it%20requires%20artful%20ways%20of%20ensuring%20that%20even%20if%20a%20government%20loses%20its%20majority%20the%20assembly%20or%20parliament%20will%20still%20complete%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E6)%20You%20also%20make%20another%20important%20point.%20You%20write%20%E2%80%9CWe%20will%20never%20be%20able%20to%20piece%20together%20a%20new%20constitution%20in%20the%20present%20day%20and%20age%20simply%20because%20innovative%20ideas%20however%20brilliant%20and%20howsoever%20encouragingly%20expressed%20in%20consultation%20papers%20and%20reports%20of%20commissions%2C%20can%20never%20give%20us%20an%20ideal%20constitution.%20In%20constitution-making%20there%20are%20hidden%20forces%20that%20must%20not%20be%20ignored%2C%20viz.%2C%20the%20spirit%20of%20persuasion%2C%20of%20accommodation%2C%20and%20of%20tolerance.%20In%20India%20%E2%80%93%20as%20in%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20%E2%80%93%20all%20three%20are%20at%20a%20very%20low%20ebb%20today.%E2%80%9D%20Can%20you%20explain%20this%20further%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E7)%20Now%20you%20have%20written%20this%20at%20a%20time%20when%20there%20is%20some%20talk%20that%20India%20needs%20a%20new%20constitution.%20No%20less%20a%20person%20than%20the%20Chairman%20of%20the%20Prime%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20Economic%20Advisory%20Council%20has%20suggested%20this.%20What%20would%20you%20say%20to%20him%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E8)%20Let%E2%80%99s%20now%20come%20to%20how%20the%20constitution%20and%20the%20rights%20it%20confers%20on%20citizens%20is%20defended%20by%20our%20judges.%20In%20your%20book%20you%20quote%20Chief%20Justice%20Chandrachud%2C%20who%20in%202017%20in%20the%20Puttaswamy%20judgement%2C%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CA%20constitutional%20democracy%20can%20survive%20when%20citizens%20have%20an%20undiluted%20assurance%20that%20the%20Rule%20of%20Law%20will%20protect%20their%20rights%20and%20liberties%20against%20any%20invasion%20by%20the%20state%20and%20that%20judicial%20remedies%20would%20be%20available%20to%20ask%20searching%20questions%20and%20expect%20answers%20when%20a%20citizen%20has%20been%20deprived%20of%20these%20most%20precious%20rights%3F%E2%80%9D%20But%20does%20even%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20live%20up%20to%20this%3F%20In%202019%20it%20effectively%20ignored%20habeas%20corpus%20cases%20in%20Kashmir.%20In%202020%20it%20turned%20a%20blind%20eye%20to%20the%20plight%20of%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20workers%20who%20had%20to%20walk%20home%20during%20the%20lockdown%20and%20its%20postponed%20critical%20cases%20like%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%20and%20Electoral%20Bonds.%20And%20right%20across%20the%20judicial%20system%20bail%20has%20become%20pretty%20difficult%20to%20get.%20So%20are%20Justice%20Chandrachud%E2%80%99s%20ringing%20words%20just%20rhetoric%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E9)%20Let%E2%80%99s%20come%20to%20how%20our%20governments%20respect%20and%20adhere%20to%20our%20constitution.%20You%20quote%20with%20appreciation%20Ambedkar%20who%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CHowever%20good%20a%20constitution%20may%20be%2C%20it%20is%20sure%20to%20turn%20out%20bad%20because%20those%20who%20are%20called%20to%20work%20it%2C%20happen%20to%20be%20a%20bad%20lot.%20However%20bad%20a%20constitution%20may%20be%2C%20it%20may%20turn%20out%20to%20be%20good%20if%20those%20who%20are%20called%20to%20work%20it%2C%20happen%20to%20be%20a%20good%20lot.%E2%80%9D%20In%20your%20opinion%20have%20our%20governments%20been%20a%20good%20lot%20or%20a%20bad%20lot%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E10)%20Finally%2C%20you%20have%20some%20very%20interesting%20things%20to%20say%20about%20the%20role%20of%20the%20Opposition%20in%20a%20democracy.%20You%20quote%20Ivor%20Jennings%20with%20approval%20when%20he%20says%3A%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20not%20untrue%20to%20say%20that%20the%20most%20important%20part%20of%20parliament%20is%20the%20Opposition%20%E2%80%A6%20the%20Opposition%20is%20at%20once%20the%20alternative%20to%20the%20government%20and%20a%20focus%20for%20the%20discontent%20of%20the%20people.%20Its%20function%20is%20almost%20as%20important%20as%20that%20of%20the%20government.%20If%20there%20be%20no%20Opposition%2C%20there%20is%20no%20democracy.%E2%80%9D%20How%20would%20you%20convince%20Narendra%20Modi%20to%20accept%20this%20view%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E11)%20You%20go%20one%20step%20further.%20Again%2C%20quoting%20Jennings%20you%20say%3A%20%E2%80%9Cattacks%20upon%20the%20government%20and%20individual%20ministers%20are%20the%20functions%20of%20the%20Opposition.%20The%20duty%20of%20the%20Opposition%20is%20to%20oppose.%E2%80%9D%20So%2C%20for%20example%2C%20when%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20fiercely%20attacks%20Narendra%20Modi%20he%E2%80%99s%20doing%20what%20his%20job%20requires%20him%20to%20do%20and%20people%20who%20call%20it%20a%20personal%20attack%20or%20vendetta%20have%20misunderstood%20the%20role%20of%20an%20Opposition%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E12)%20But%20you%20do%20have%20one%20caution%20or%20warning%20for%20the%20Opposition.%20Quoting%20a%20British%20document%20you%20say%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Opposition%20has%20no%20right%20to%20obstruct%2C%20in%20the%20sense%20of%20making%20parliament%20barren%20or%20unproductive.%E2%80%9D%20So%20does%20this%20mean%20that%20the%20Arun%20Jaitley%20and%20Sushma%20Swaraj%20view%2C%20now%20practiced%20by%20the%20Opposition%2C%20that%20obstructing%20parliament%20is%20a%20legitimate%20parliamentary%20tactic%2C%20is%20deeply%20mistaken%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWatch%20the%20interview%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DlaWeb3Qqq_k%26ab_channel%3DTheWire%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694604358000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fvideo-karan-thapar-fali-nariman-new-constitution%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Fali%20Nariman%2C%20who%20is%20widely%20considered%20India%E2%80%99s%20greatest%20living%20expert%20on%20the%20constitution%2C%20said%20that%20it%20is%20impossible%20to%20write%20a%20new%20one%20in%20the%20atmosphere%20that%20prevails%20in%20the%20country%20today.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fvideo-karan-thapar-fali-nariman-new-constitution%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Shilpa%3A%20Raj%20%26amp%3B%20I%20have%20middle-class%20upbringing%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694604248000%2C%22