u-s-hid-533-million-in-hedge-fund-camshaft-run-from-miami-ihop-lenders-say%23xj4y7vzkg%5C%22%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20this%20hedge%20fund%20was%20established%20by%20William%20C.%20Morton%2C%20at%20the%20age%20of%2023.%20And%20these%20lenders%20allege%20that%20Byju%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Chid%E2%80%9D%20the%20money%20in%20this%20hedge%20fund.%20They%20contend%20that%20Morton%E2%80%99s%20fund%20received%20this%20substantial%20amount%20despite%20his%20apparent%20lack%20of%20formal%20investment%20training.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20court%20documents%20reveal%20that%20luxury%20cars%2C%20including%20a%202023%20Ferrari%20Roma%2C%20a%202020%20Lamborghini%20Hurac%C3%A1n%20EVO%2C%20and%20a%202014%20Rolls-Royce%20Wraith%2C%20have%20been%20registered%20in%20Morton%E2%80%99s%20name%20since%20the%20transfer%20took%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20in%20a%202020%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission%20filing%2C%20Camshaft%20noted%20its%20main%20business%20address%20as%20285%20NW%2042nd%20Ave.%20This%20address%20actually%20houses%20an%20IHOP%20restaurant%20(a%20pancake%20shop)%20in%20Miami%E2%80%99s%20Little%20Havana%20area.%20The%20neighboring%20businesses%20include%20a%20drive-through%20car%20wash%20and%20a%20strip%20mall%20featuring%20a%20massage%20parlour%20and%20a%20sandwich%20shop%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20address%20had%20been%20home%20to%20the%20IHOP%20for%20decades%2C%20%3Cem%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20IHOP%20employee%20told%20%3Cem%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20she%20had%20never%20heard%20of%20Morton%2C%20Camshaft%20Capital%20Fund%2C%20or%20Byju%E2%80%99s%2C%20indicating%20no%20business%20activity%20related%20to%20the%20hedge%20fund%20at%20that%20location.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fem%3E%20also%20noted%20that%20Camshaft%2C%20in%20an%20unrelated%20lawsuit%20filed%20by%20the%20hedge%20fund%2C%20said%20its%20principal%20place%20of%20business%20is%20in%20the%20Virgin%20Islands.%20This%20lawsuit%20was%20filed%20in%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lenders%E2%80%99%20agent%2C%20Glas%20Trust%2C%20argued%20that%20Byju%E2%80%99s%20has%20worked%20hard%20to%20hide%20the%20%24533%20million%20owed%20to%20borrowers%2C%20intending%20to%20slow%20down%20and%20obstruct%20creditors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EByju%E2%80%99s%20has%20denied%20these%20allegations%2C%20reported%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businesstoday.in%2Fentrepreneurship%2Fstart-up%2Fstory%2Fbyjus-refutes-accusations-of-concealing-533-million-in-hedge-fund-cites-credit-agreement-compliance-398189-2023-09-13%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Today%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20a%20commercially%20prudent%20borrower%20and%20like%20any%20other%20large%20corporate%20treasury%2C%20Byju%E2%80%99s%20Alpha%20has%20made%20investments%20in%20a%20multi-hundred%20billion%20dollar%20fund%20with%20high%20security%20fixed%20income%20instruments.%20Our%20Credit%20Agreement%20with%20the%20lenders%20does%20not%20prohibit%20or%20restrict%20the%20movement%20or%20investment%20of%20monies%20disbursed%20thereunder.%20There%20is%20no%20requirement%20for%20Byju%E2%80%99s%20to%20maintain%20cash%20as%20collateral%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20Byju%E2%80%99s%20spokesperson%20told%20%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Today%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGlas%20Trust%2C%20the%20agent%20for%20the%20creditors%2C%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20informed%20Camshaft%20about%20the%20lawsuit%2C%20the%20fund%E2%80%99s%20lawyers%20told%20%3Cem%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fem%3E.%20%E2%80%9CCamshaft%20vigorously%20denies%20the%20statements%20made%20in%20Glas%20Trust%20Company%E2%80%99s%E2%80%9D%20court%20filing%2C%20Camshaft%20lawyer%20David%20Massey%20said%20in%20an%20emailed%20statement%2C%20noted%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20else%20have%20the%20lenders%20said%20in%20their%20court%20filings%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lenders%20argued%20that%20the%20%24533%20million%20transferred%20is%20collateral%20for%20a%20%241.2%20billion%20loan%2C%20and%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20dispute%20between%20Byju%E2%80%99s%20and%20the%20lenders%20regarding%20the%20loan%20status.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20that%20Byju%E2%80%99s%20is%20attempting%20to%20negotiate%20a%20deal%20with%20creditors%20and%20proposing%20to%20buy%20back%20the%20loan%20within%20six%20months%2C%20through%20selling%20overseas%20assets%20to%20private%20equity%20and%20strategic%20investors.%20(A%20loan%20buy%20back%20occurs%20when%20a%20borrower%20repays%20a%20portion%20of%20the%20loan%20for%20less%20than%20the%20promised%20amount.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lenders%20also%20highlighted%20that%20Byju%E2%80%99s%20sent%20the%20money%20to%20Camshaft%2C%20which%20appears%20to%20cater%20to%20smaller%20clients%20and%20accepts%20investments%20as%20low%20as%20%2450%2C000%20for%20a%20hedge%20fund.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20missing%20cash%20is%20at%20the%20center%20of%20the%20lenders%E2%80%99%20actions%2C%20the%20report%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20lenders%20had%20gained%20control%20of%20the%20Byju%E2%80%99s%20unit%20that%20issued%20the%20debt%2C%20but%20the%20money%20had%20already%20disappeared.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20May%2C%20Byju%E2%80%99s%20Alpha%E2%80%99s%20lawyer%20had%20said%2C%20during%20a%20court%20hearing%2C%20that%20the%20company%20was%20trying%20to%20protect%20the%20money%20from%20predatory%20lenders.%20The%20company%20had%20a%20right%20to%20transfer%20the%20money%20under%20the%20loan%20agreement%2C%20the%20lawyer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EByju%E2%80%99s%20accused%20the%20lenders%20of%20seeking%20control%20of%20the%20entire%20ed-tech%20empire%20led%20by%20its%20founder%2C%20Byju%20Raveendran.%20It%20had%20asked%20a%20Delaware%20judge%20to%20reject%20the%20default%20declared%20by%20Glas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20startup%20was%20founded%20in%202015%2C%20Byju%E2%80%99s%20has%20received%20significant%20investments%20from%20major%20players%20in%20the%20tech%20industry%2C%20such%20as%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%E2%80%99s%20Chan%20Zuckerberg%20Initiative%2C%20Silver%20Lake%20Management%2C%20and%20Naspers%20Ltd.%20Last%20year%2C%20Byju%E2%80%99s%20was%20valued%20at%20over%20%2420%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lenders%E2%80%99%20lawsuit%20aims%20to%20trace%20the%20money%20and%20recover%20any%20excess%20management%20fees%20paid%20to%20Camshaft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20the%20time%20of%20the%20report%2C%20Camshaft%20had%20not%20yet%20filed%20a%20response%20to%20the%20lawsuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBackstory%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20November%202021%2C%20the%20company%20had%20raised%20a%20%241.2%20billion%20term%20loan%20from%20a%20group%20of%20US-based%20creditors.%20However%2C%20in%20June%20this%20year%2C%20Byju%E2%80%99s%20missed%20a%20%2440%20million%20interest%20payment%20on%20this%20loan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlpha%20is%20the%20borrowing%20entity%20under%20the%20Term%20Loan%20B.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20term%20loan%20provides%20borrowers%20with%20a%20lump%20sum%20of%20cash%20upfront%20in%20exchange%20for%20specific%20borrowing%20terms.%20Borrowers%20agree%20to%20pay%20their%20lenders%20a%20fixed%20amount%20over%20a%20certain%20repayment%20schedule%20with%20either%20a%20fixed%20or%20floating%20interest%20rate.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20company%20missed%20the%20quarterly%20payment%20schedule%20on%20June%205%2C%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Ftech%2Ftechnology%2Fbyjus-files-suit-challenging-loan-acceleration-seeks-redwoods-disqualification%2Farticleshow%2F100781321.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Esued%3C%2Fa%3E%20its%20lenders%20and%20related%20entities%20for%20accelerating%20the%20repayment%20of%20the%20term%20loan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EByju%E2%80%99s%20declared%20that%20it%20would%20withhold%20any%20further%20payments%2C%20including%20interest%2C%20to%20the%20lenders%20until%20the%20court%20settles%20the%20dispute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20a%20matter%20of%20fact%2C%20the%20Delaware%20cour