%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F11%2F01140646%2F2019_10img31_Oct_2019_PTI10_31_2019_000257B.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20South%20Asia%20has%20some%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20only%20areas%20where%20nitrogen%20dioxide%20(NO%3Csub%3E2%3C%2Fsub%3E)%20levels%20are%20increasing%2C%20an%20analysis%20by%20State%20of%20Global%20Air%20(SOGA)%20has%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESOGA%20is%20a%20research%20and%20outreach%20initiative%20that%20aims%20to%20provide%20meaningful%20information%20about%20air%20quality%20in%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20published%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.stateofglobalair.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fdocuments%2F2023-09%2Fsoga_reg._aq_snapshot_9-11-23_final.pdf%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98snapshot%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20air%20quality%20in%20the%20South%20Asia%20region%20on%20Tuesday%20(September%2012)%20that%20draws%20from%20a%20global%20air%20quality%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.stateofglobalair.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fdocuments%2F2022-08%2F2022-soga-cities-report.pdf%5C%22%3Eanalysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20concluded%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20snapshot%20finds%20that%20while%20levels%20of%20NO%3Csub%3E2%3C%2Fsub%3E%20%E2%80%93%20a%20pollutant%20belonging%20to%20the%20highly%20reactive%20nitrogen%20oxides%20(NO%3Csub%3Ex%3C%2Fsub%3E)%20group%20of%20gases%20%E2%80%93%20have%20declined%20in%20North%20America%2C%20Western%20Europe%20and%20China%20over%20recent%20years%2C%20they%20have%20been%20increasing%20in%20South%20Asia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20%E2%80%9Cfuelled%20by%20large-scale%20programs%20to%20expand%20access%20to%20energy%20to%20households%2C%20expanding%20industries%20and%20increases%20in%20vehicle%20ownership%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20major%20sources%20of%20NO%3Csub%3E2%3C%2Fsub%3E%20are%20coal-based%20energy%20production%2C%20industrial%20processes%20and%20on-road%20transportation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExposure%20to%20the%20gas%20can%20irritate%20the%20airways%2C%20aggravate%20existing%20respiratory%20diseases%20and%20increase%20the%20susceptibility%20to%20new%20ones%2C%20and%20heighten%20the%20risk%20of%20asthma%20development%20in%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20data%20from%202019%2C%20Bengaluru%20and%20Hyderabad%20top%20the%20list%20of%20major%20South%20Asian%20cities%20in%20terms%20of%20population-weighted%20NO%3Csub%3E2%3C%2Fsub%3E%20exposure%2C%20SOGA%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2F31191817%2F2022_10img31_Oct_2022_PTI10_31_2022_000190B-1024x691.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2F31191817%2F2022_10img31_Oct_2022_PTI10_31_2022_000190B-1024x691.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2F31191817%2F2022_10img31_Oct_2022_PTI10_31_2022_000190B-300x203.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2F31191817%2F2022_10img31_Oct_2022_PTI10_31_2022_000190B.jpg%201200w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-626666%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22567%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ENO%3Csub%3E2%3C%2Fsub%3E%20is%20also%20a%20key%20marker%20for%20traffic-related%20air%20pollution%2C%20the%20snapshot%20said.%20Photo%3A%20PTI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20added%20that%20although%20South%20Asia%20stands%20out%20for%20the%20increase%20in%20its%20NO%3Csub%3Ex%3C%2Fsub%3E%20emissions%2C%20NO%3Csub%3E2%3C%2Fsub%3E%20emissions%20are%20low%20here%20compared%20to%20other%20regions%20in%20the%20world%2C%20and%20some%20countries%20in%20South%20Asia%20have%20NO%3Csub%3E2%3C%2Fsub%3E%20quality%20standards%20in%20line%20with%20interim%20targets%20recommended%20by%20the%20WHO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20cited%20a%20policy%20action%20from%20India%2C%20namely%20the%20Union%20government%20moving%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2Fnewsite%2Fprintrelease.aspx%3Frelid%3D134232%5C%22%3Edirectly%20from%20the%20BS-IV%20emission%20norms%20to%20BS-VI%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20an%20example%20of%20an%20initiative%20that%20will%20significantly%20reduce%20NO%3Csub%3Ex%3C%2Fsub%3E%20emissions%20and%20bring%20%E2%80%9Cclean%20air%20dividends%20in%20the%20next%20decade%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20India%2C%20addressing%20source-specific%20emissions%20(for%20example%2C%20transportation)%20have%20begun%20to%20show%20dividends.%20In%20fact%2C%20satellite-based%20estimates%20indicate%20that%20NO%3Csub%3E2%3C%2Fsub%3E%20levels%20may%20be%20beginning%20to%20decline%20in%20some%20Indian%20cities%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20snapshot%20also%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20another%20major%20air%20pollutant%2C%20PM%3Csub%3E2.5%3C%2Fsub%3E%2C%20SOGA%20noted%20that%20exposure%20it%20to%20remains%20high%20in%20South%20Asian%20cities.%20Less%20than%201%25%20of%20these%20cities%20meet%20the%20WHO%E2%80%99s%20PM%3Csub%3E2.5%3C%2Fsub%3E%20guidelines%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20list%20it%20provided%20of%20major%20South%20Asian%20cities%20with%20the%20most%20population-weighted%20PM%3Csub%3E2.5%3C%2Fsub%3E%20exposure%20as%20of%202019%20had%20Delhi%20and%20Kolkata%20in%20the%20first%20and%20second%20positions%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20same%20two%20cities%20topped%20the%20SOGA%E2%80%99s%20list%20for%20major%20cities%20across%20the%20world.%20Beijing%20came%20in%20at%20a%20farther%20ninth%20and%20Mumbai%20clocked%20in%20at%2014th.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPM%3Csub%3E2.5%3C%2Fsub%3E%20is%20any%20particulate%20matter%20that%20has%20a%20maximum%20width%20of%202.5%20micrometres%20(0.0025%20mm).%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fairquality.gsfc.nasa.gov%2Fparticulate-matter%5C%22%3Emajority%20of%20air%20pollution%20deaths%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20associated%20with%20PM%3Csub%3E2.5%3C%2Fsub%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESOGA%E2%80%99s%20snapshot%20said%20that%2034%25%20of%20deaths%20in%20South%20Asia%E2%80%99s%2020%20most%20populated%20cities%20are%20linked%20to%20exposure%20to%20PM%3Csub%3E2.5%3C%2Fsub%3E%2C%20and%20that%20Indians%20lose%201.5%20years%20of%20their%20lives%20to%20PM%3Csub%3E2.5%3C%2Fsub%3E%20pollution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20study%20by%20the%20University%20of%20Chicago%20Energy%20Policy%20Institute%20last%20month%20said%20that%20particulate%20pollution%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22file%3A%2FC%3A%2FUsers%2Fairsu%2FDownloads%2FIndia-FactSheet-2023_Final.pdf%5C%22%3Etakes%205.3%20years%20off%20the%20lifespan%20of%20an%20average%20Indian%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20that%20if%20India%20were%20to%20reduce%20particulate%20pollution%20to%20meet%20the%20WHO%20guideline%2C%20Delhiites%20stand%20to%20gain%20close%20to%2012%20years%20in%20life%20expectancy.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694593535000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F11%2F01140646%2F2019_10img31_Oct_2019_PTI10_31_2019_000257B.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fnitrogen-oxides-emissions-increasing-in-south-asia-says-soga-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20%E2%80%98snapshot%E2%80%99%20recently%20released%20by%20State%20of%20Global%20Air%20finds%20that%20the%20trend%20in%20South%20Asia%20is%20the%20reverse%20of%20what%20has%20been%20observed%20in%20North%20America%2C%20Western%20Europe%20and%20China.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fnitrogen-oxides-emissions-increasing-in-south-asia-says-soga-report%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22UK%20'closely%20monitoring'%20spread%20of%20fatal%20cow%20disease%20in%20Europe%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694593260000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe