oved%20the%20high%20court%20a%20day%20ago%2C%20on%20September%2012%2C%20seeking%20the%20cancellation%20of%20this%20judicial%20remand%20in%20the%20case%2C%20along%20with%20its%20quashing%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fandhra-pradesh-hc-stays-chandrababu-naidu-trial-court%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Allahabad%20HC%20Chief%20Justice's%20Order%20to%20Withdraw%20Gyanvapi%20Cases%20From%20Judge%20Cites%20'Judicial%20Propriety'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F03%2F08080324%2FAllahabad_high_court_PTI-copy.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20the%20Allahabad%20high%20court%20has%20withdrawn%20cases%20related%20to%20the%20challenge%20over%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Mosque%2C%20which%20is%20adjacent%20to%20the%20Kashi%20Vishwanath%20temple%20in%20Varanasi%2C%20from%20the%20current%20bench%2C%20citing%20judicial%20propriety%20and%20discipline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fcities%2Flucknow%2Fallahabad-high-court-cj-withdraws-all-gyanvapi-cases-from-single-judge-bench-8937399%2F%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20an%20administrative%20order%2C%20dated%20August%2011%2C%20in%20which%20Chief%20Justice%20Pritinker%20Diwaker%20has%20called%20for%20the%20withdrawal%20of%20cases%20from%20the%20single-judge%20bench%20of%20Justice%20Prakash%20Padia.%20CJ%20Diwaker%20cited%20this%20order%20again%20on%20August%2028.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20called%20for%20the%20fresh%20nomination%20of%20a%20bench.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20site%20of%20the%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fshivling-kashi-vishwanath-temple-gyanvapi%5C%22%3E%20Gyanvapi%20Mosque%20has%20been%20a%20space%20of%20communal%20politics%20since%20before%C2%A0five%20Hindu%20women%20moved%20a%20Varanasi%20court%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20August%202021%20seeking%20permission%20to%20worship%20an%20image%20of%20Maa%20Shringar%20Gauri%20located%20on%20the%20back%20wall%20of%20the%20Gyanvapi%20mosque.%20They%20also%20sought%20permission%20to%20worship%20all%20the%20%E2%80%9Cvisible%20and%20invisible%E2%80%9D%20deities%20within%20the%20mosque%20and%20old%20temple%20complex.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20temple%20side%20litigants%2C%20the%20mosque%20was%20built%20on%20the%20site%20of%20the%20original%20Kashi%20Vishwanath%20temple.%20The%20mosque%E2%80%99s%20litigants%20have%20maintained%20that%20the%20mosque%20was%20built%20on%20Waqf%20premises%2C%20and%20that%20the%20Places%20of%20Worship%20(Special%20Provisions)%20Act%2C%201991%20barred%20changing%20the%20character%20of%20any%20place%20of%20worship%20as%20it%20existed%20on%20August%2015%2C%201947.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Chief%20Justice%E2%80%99s%20order%20notes%20that%20the%20cases%20were%20heard%20on%20January%2018%2C%202021%2C%20by%20the%20court%2C%20and%20on%20several%20following%20dates.%20Judgment%20was%20reserved%20on%20the%20matter%20on%20March%2015%2C%202021%2C%20but%20was%20not%20delivered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20cases%20nevertheless%20continued%20to%20be%20listed%20before%20the%20same%20court%20even%20after%20the%20concerned%20learned%20Single%20Judge%20ceased%20to%20have%20jurisdiction%20in%20the%20matter%20as%20per%20roster%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20Chief%20Justice%E2%80%99s%20order%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20order%20further%20says%20that%20the%20facts%20of%20this%20case%20point%20to%20%E2%80%9Ca%20more%20troubled%20scenario%20of%20procedural%20aberration.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20Chief%20Justice%20says%20that%20procedure%20was%20not%20observed%20on%20these%20cases%2C%20where%20despite%20passing%20of%20successive%20orders%20for%20reserving%20judgment%2C%20cases%20were%20listed%20once%20again%20with%20the%20same%20judge%20%E2%80%9Cwithout%20allowing%20the%20parent%20section%20in%20the%20office%20to%20have%20access%20to%20the%20records%20of%20these%20cases%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20%E2%80%9Cthis%20concern%20of%20propriety%E2%80%9D%20which%20%E2%80%9Ccompelled%E2%80%9D%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20to%20pass%20orders%20on%20the%20administrative%20side%20on%20August%2011%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EExpress%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20registry%2C%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20said%20in%20his%20latest%20August%2028%20order%2C%20has%20further%20clarified%20that%20the%20records%20of%20these%20cases%20were%20never%20sent%20to%20the%20parent%20section%20for%20due%20process%20to%20be%20followed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20per%20the%20registry%2C%20the%20parent%20section%20responsible%20for%20listing%20of%20the%20cases%20before%20the%20Court%20had%20no%20access%20to%20the%20records%20of%20the%20cases%20as%20the%20files%20were%20never%20sent%20to%20the%20registry%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EObservance%20of%20procedure%20instils%20faith%20in%20the%20justice%20dispensation%20system%2C%20the%20judge%20added%2C%20noting%20that%20a%20judge%20is%20expected%20to%20decided%20cases%20before%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694585720000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F03%2F08080324%2FAllahabad_high_court_PTI-copy.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fallahabad-high-court-chief-justice-gyanvapi-kashi-vishwanath-cases%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'The%20cases%20nevertheless%20continued%20to%20be%20listed%20before%20the%20same%20court%20even%20after%20the%20concerned%20learned%20Single%20Judge%20ceased%20to%20have%20jurisdiction%20in%20the%20matter%20as%20per%20roster.'%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fallahabad-high-court-chief-justice-gyanvapi-k